---
- name: Firewald and SELinux 
  hosts: all
  become: true
  tasks:
    - name: Firewall
      ansible.posix.firewalld:
        permanent: true
        port: 80/tcp
        state: enabled


    - name: Disable SELinux
      ansible.posix.selinux:
        state: disabled
******************************************
to check the target node if the port is really opened , rmrmber :
systemctl-cmd --state
firewall-cmd --reload
firewall-cmd --list-ports

it should show : 80/tcp
Done.
